analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Equilibrium persists amid nascent volatility expansion. The GMS equilibrium at 50 signals a transitionary regime where liquidity convexity remains constrained despite stable net liquidity. While equity indices demonstrate localized resilience, the 4.13% expansion in the VIX and flat OGV vectors indicate a degradation of risk-on momentum. Narrowing credit spread compression and industrial-sector headwinds suggest a deceleration in the fiscal-monetary nexus, necessitating a mitigation of idiosyncratic exposure as the market navigates this neutral volatility pivot. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
